-- Spain Working to Release Journalist Kidnapped in Syria, Efe Says
-- B y   E m m a   R o s s - T h o m a s
-- 2013-09-24T10:33:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-09-24/spain-working-to-release-journalist-kidnapped-in-syria-efe-says.html
Spain  is working to secure the
release of Marc Marginedas, a journalist who was kidnapped in
Syria this month, state news agency Efe reported, citing
Interior Minister Jorge Fernandez Diaz.  Marginedas, who works for  El Periodico  newspaper, is being
held by a group that is close to al-Qaeda, Efe cited the
minister as saying today in Madrid. Marginedas, 46, has been
held since Sept. 4, the agency reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Emma Ross-Thomas in Madrid at 
 erossthomas@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
